      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">12.203</ph> Procedures for solicitation,
evaluation, and award.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d710e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2021-03 February 16, 2021" class="- topic/ph ">Contracting <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-016?>officers<?FM MARKER [Why] Revise section 12.203 by redesignating the text as paragraph (a) and adding paragraph (b).?></ph> shall
use the policies unique to the acquisition of commercial items prescribed
in this part in conjunction with the policies and procedures for
solicitation, evaluation and award prescribed in <xref href="Part_13.dita#FAR_Part_13"
                        base="i1112458"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  13</xref>, Simplified
Acquisition Procedures; <xref href="Part_14.dita#FAR_Part_14"
                        base="i1111055"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  14</xref> Sealed
Bidding; or <xref href="Part_15.dita#FAR_Part_15"
                        base="i1109360"
                        outputclass="fm:Part"
                        class="- topic/xref ">part  15</xref>, Contracting
by Negotiation, as appropriate for the particular acquisition. The
contracting officer may use the streamlined procedure for soliciting
offers for commercial items prescribed in <xref href="12.603.dita#FAR_12_603"
                        base="i1112649"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">12.603</xref>. For acquisitions
of commercial items exceeding the simplified acquisition threshold
but not exceeding $7.5 million ($15 million for acquisitions as
described in <xref href="13.500.dita#FAR_13_500"
                        base="i1111260"
                        outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                        class="- topic/xref ">13.500</xref> (c)), including
options, contracting activities may use any of the simplified procedures
authorized by <xref href="Subpart_13.5.dita#FAR_Subpart_13_5"
                        base="i1111258"
                        outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                        class="- topic/xref ">subpart  13.5</xref>.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d710e39" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  <ph rev="FAC 2021-03 February 16, 2021" class="- topic/ph ">Contracting <?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-016?>officers shall
ensure the criteria at <xref href="15.101-2.dita#FAR_15_101_2"
                           outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                           class="- topic/xref ">15.101-2</xref>(c) are met when
using the lowest price technically acceptable source selection process.<?FM MARKER [Why] Revise section 12.203 by redesignating the text as paragraph (a) and adding paragraph (b).?></ph>
               </p>
            </li>
         </ol>
      </conbody>
